com.mobilab.accountservice.bussiness.message

Class MyRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mobilab.accountservice.bussiness.message.MyRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PartitioningKeyGetter, java.io.Serializable

    public class MyRequest
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, PartitioningKeyGetter
    encapsulates any request which is sent from gateway to business handler. it contains all information required in any type of the request. the nullable fields could be null and there is no need to serialize them in Kafka topics.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • account

        private Account account
        if message is read request, it only contains accountNo. if message is update request, it contains accountNo and the updated version of account object. if message is insert request, it contains accountNo and initial fields of account object. if message is withdrawal or deposit, it only contains accountNo. if message is transfer request, it only contains accountNo of the source.

      • financialAmount

        private java.lang.Double financialAmount
        in financial requests (withdrawal, deposit, transfer) shows the amount of money. in other kinds of request is null.

      • financialAccountNo2

        private java.lang.String financialAccountNo2
        in transfer requests shows the accountNo of the destination account. in other kinds of request is null.
